code: protected Endpoint createEndpoint(String uri, String remaining, Map<String, Object> parameters) throws Exception {     SnsConfiguration configuration = this.configuration.copy().     setProperties(configuration, parameters).     if (remaining == null || remaining.trim().length() == 0) {         throw new IllegalArgumentException("Topic name must be specified.").     }     if (remaining.startsWith("arn:")) {         String[] parts = remaining.split(":").         if (parts.length != 6 || !parts[2].equals("sns")) {             throw new IllegalArgumentException("Topic arn must be in format arn:aws:sns:region:account:name.").         }         configuration.setTopicArn(remaining).         configuration.setRegion(Regions.fromName(parts[3]).toString()).     } else {         configuration.setTopicName(remaining).     }     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getAccessKey())) {         setAccessKey(accessKey).     }     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getSecretKey())) {         setSecretKey(secretKey).     }     if (ObjectHelper.isEmpty(configuration.getRegion())) {         setRegion(region).     }     if (configuration.getAmazonSNSClient() == null && (configuration.getAccessKey() == null || configuration.getSecretKey() == null)) {         throw new IllegalArgumentException("AmazonSNSClient or accessKey and secretKey must be specified").     }     SnsEndpoint endpoint = new SnsEndpoint(uri, this, configuration).     return endpoint. }
/**  * The AWS SNS default configuration  */ public void setConfiguration(SnsConfiguration configuration) {     this.configuration = configuration. }
/**  * Amazon AWS Access Key  */ public void setAccessKey(String accessKey) {     configuration.setAccessKey(accessKey). }
/**  * Amazon AWS Secret Key  */ public void setSecretKey(String secretKey) {     configuration.setSecretKey(secretKey). }
